State MSM Profile: Florida

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Florida

An estimated 340,163 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Florida in 2013, representing 7.6% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 7,283,572 adult men of Florida, 4.7% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was greater than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Florida resided in central counties of large metropolitan areas (47.1%). Including both central and fringe counties, 79.9% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Florida, 2013

MSM in Florida Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Florida, Miami-Dade County had the largest population of MSM at 59,732, representing 17.6% of all MSM in the state. Liberty County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Florida at 12.6%. This was greater than the percentage for Florida as a whole, which was 4.7% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Florida Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Miami-Fort Lauderdale-West Palm Beach Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Miami-Fort Lauderdale-West Palm Beach MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Florida at 141,088, or 41.5% of all MSM in the state. Of the 2,131,593 adult men in Miami-Fort Lauderdale-West Palm Beach, an estimated 6.6% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
